In a statement released by the White House Office of the Press Secretary on January 22, 2014, the President reaffirms his commitment to the guiding principle of the Supreme Court decision in Roe v. Wade. He believes that every woman should have the right to make her own choices about her body and her health. The President also emphasizes the importance of protecting a woman's access to safe and affordable healthcare, as well as her constitutional right to privacy and reproductive freedom. He expresses a desire to reduce the number of unintended pregnancies, support maternal and child health, and create safe and healthy communities for all children. The President believes that everyone in the country deserves the same freedom and opportunities to fulfill their dreams.